Package Elements

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Event
    Provides an interface for Event classes.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AttackEvent
    A class used to describe instantiations of a pitch event
    AttackEventChord
    A class extending the AttackEvent class to represent the instantiation of multiple pitches
    Chord
    A class that encapsulates multiple keys to be instantiated at the same point in time.
    ConcreteScale
    A concrete Scale extends the Scale class to encapsulate a Scale made up of specific pitches.
    EventStream
    An EventStream is used to encapsulate a stream of Event objects which is used to encapsulate a piece of music.*
    Key
    A Key class is used to encapsulates details concerning a single pitch event.
    Pair<T,T2>
    This Pair class is used to combine two objects into one.
    RestEvent
    Extends the Event class to describe a musical rest.
    Scale
    A class used to encapsulate a diatonic scale.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    ArticulationEnum
    A set of enums describing different musical articulations
    DurationEnum
    Used to describe the length of a pitch event in terms of metrical beats.
    DynamicsEnum
    A list of dynamics that can be associated with an AttackEvent or a group of music.
    KeyLetterEnum
    The KeyLetterEnum is used to describe key positions within a scale for a pitch, and is used in conjunction with the KeyPositionEnum to describe a pitch position.
    KeyPositionEnum
    Describes the position of a KeyLetterEnum in order to describe a specific pitch position.
